<h2>MySQL</h2>
<h3>Introduction</h3>
<p>
  MySQL is a database management system created by MySQL AB.
  It's currently one of the most popular databases in the Open Source community and most often on by default in PHP.
</p>
<p>From their homepage:</p>
<div class="quote">MySQL is the world's most popular Open Source Database, designed for speed, power and precision in mission critical, heavy load use.</div>
<p>More information can be found on <a href="http://www.mysql.com">mysql.com</a>.</p>

<h3>Details</h3>
<p>MySQL is a good choice for handling most western languages, however it's currently not the best choice for Unicode or non-western languages.</p>

<h3>Installation</h3>
<p>By using the <tt class="option">--with-mysql</tt> configuration option you enable PHP to access MySQL databases. If you use this option without specifying the path to MySQL, PHP will use the built-in MySQL client libraries.</p>

<p>More information on the MySQL extension can be found at <a href="http://www.php.net/manual/en/ref.mysql.php">php.net</a>.</p>
